    "system": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><em>You form stone into a different shape. Tracing the stone with a finger, it is molded like clay into a shape you describe in a gravely voice.</em></p><p><strong>Utility Spell</strong></p><p>This spell affects a stone object of medium size or smaller, or a section of stone no more than 5 feet in any dimension. You can do the following:</p><ul><li><p>You can clear a 5 ft. cube of stone (potentially opening a passage) or expand stone to take up an additional 5 ft.</p></li><li><p>If you use this spell to seal a stone door or object shut, the object has immunity to &amp;reference[poison] and &amp;reference[psychic] damage, resistance to non-adamantine &amp;reference[bludgeoning], &amp;reference[piercing], and &amp;reference[slashing] damage, and resistance to &amp;reference[cold], &amp;reference[fire], &amp;reference[lightning], and &amp;reference[necrotic] damage. It must take 10 damage from a single attack to be broken open.</p></li></ul>",
